tokenizer_name: anthropic-approx-bpe
tokenizer_version: 1.0.0
tokenizer_sha: sha256:3c0c1f82c5e5b09f1e4d6b4d1c4d85f6c1c2a7b8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0
source: plugins/gaia/test/scripts/token-reduction/tokenize.mjs
notes: |
  Deterministic byte-based approximation tokenizer pinned for NFR-048 measurements.
  The `tokens` count is ceil(prompt_bytes / 4) — the well-known approximation
  used by _memory/config.yaml archival.token_approximation and by the Anthropic
  "tokens ≈ chars / 4" rule of thumb. This is a SURROGATE tokenizer for
  before/after comparison purposes only; it is NOT the production-grade
  Anthropic tokenizer. Determinism is guaranteed because the function is pure
  over the captured prompt bytes. The SHA above pins this contract — any
  change to the tokenizer algorithm MUST change this SHA and re-run every
  measurement from scratch.
